1)  ‚è∞ BreakTimer

Build a Java program that acts like a digital break timer.
It will count down from a specified number of minutes and show the time left in MM:SS format.
When the timer ends, it will display a message
"BREAK TIME IS OVER. PLEASE COME BACK TO CLASS"

-Create a new class BreakTimer

‚úÖ Part 1. The method setBreakTime(int minutes) will:
    ‚Ä¢	Check if the minutes are greater than 0.
    ‚Ä¢	Print a message showing the break time duration and the expected end time.
    ‚Ä¢	Start a countdown that shows minutes and seconds remaining.

‚úÖ Part 2: Time Formatting and Countdown
	1.	Display the time left in MM:SS format and update it every second using:
	‚Ä¢	Thread.sleep() for waiting
	‚Ä¢	Nested loops for minutes and seconds
	‚Ä¢	System.out.print() with carriage return \r to update the same line

‚úÖ Part 3: Add Estimated End Time
	1.	Create a method named addMinutes(int minutes) that:
	‚Ä¢	Gets the current system time
	‚Ä¢	Adds the break duration
	‚Ä¢	Formats the end time in hh:mm AM/PM format using the Java Time API

‚úÖ Part 4: Add main() and call the method setBreakTime(15);

